TITLE: Parisians vote to ban e-scooters from French capital
SUMMARY: Cities worldwide are tightening regulations on e-scooters, limiting the number of operators, as well as speed and where they can park

TITLE: Russian forces claim to 'legally' control Bakhmut, but Ukraine says fighting is still raging
SUMMARY: Ukrainian officials said fierce fighting was ongoing Monday in the heart of the eastern city that has become the focal point of the war

TITLE: U.S. citizen sentenced to 20 years in prison for joining Islamic State group
SUMMARY: Emraan Ali, 55, a U.S. citizen born in Trinidad and Tobago, was sentenced Tuesday in Miami federal court, according to court records. He pleaded guilty in November to conspiring to provide material support to a foreign terrorist organization

TITLE: 'Evil eye' jewelry that was used to protect a young girl 1,800 years ago is unveiled in Israel
SUMMARY: Golden jewelry meant to protect young girls in Roman times on their journey to the afterlife has been put on display 50 years after the discovery in Jerusalem

TITLE: In Mexico, reproductive rights network helps U.S. women obtain abortions
SUMMARY: An abortion model in which no travel, clinics or prescriptions are needed has sparked requests for help from the U.S

TITLE: Finland turns to the right as it prepares to enter NATO
SUMMARY: Prime Minister Sanna Marin's defeat is the latest setback for the left amid a larger shift to conservative and nationalist parties across Europe in recent times

TITLE: Russia blames Ukraine and arrests suspect after bomb kills prominent pro-war blogger
SUMMARY: Vladlen Tatarsky was killed in a bombing attack Sunday night as he held an event at a cafe in the center of St. Petersburg

TITLE: Meet the 'world's deepest fish,' filmed for the first time at bone-crushing depths
SUMMARY: Researchers using an autonomous deep-ocean vessel recorded the unknown snailfish species at a bone-crushing depth of 27,349 feet

TITLE: McCarthy to meet with Taiwanese president in visit China calls a 'provocation'
SUMMARY: The top Republican, who is second in line for the U.S. presidency, announced Monday that he would meet with Taiwan's president, Tsai Ing-wen

TITLE: Indian opposition leader Rahul Gandhi avoids prison as he appeals defamation verdict
SUMMARY: A court suspended Gandhi’s two-year sentence for mocking the prime minister’s surname, which resulted in his expulsion from Parliament
